If I ordered something else
when we're dining, I didn't--

21:00.300 --> 21:01.260
Right, right.

21:01.343 --> 21:03.845
-Maybe that looks more weird. Yeah.
Yeah.

21:03.929 --> 21:06.223
Everything is so powerful. Right.

21:06.306 --> 21:09.518
And it's these invisible
assumptions we walk around with,

21:09.601 --> 21:13.063
or things we know, but don't really
know why they're a problem.

21:14.189 --> 21:16.650
Fried chicken dark
with black, cornbread dressing.

21:16.733 --> 21:17.734
-Fried chicken white.
-Thanks.

21:17.818 --> 21:20.362
Beautiful. That looks great.
-Mmm-hmm.

21:21.655 --> 21:26.243
So you don't feel like... Fried chicken
explosion around the world.

21:26.326 --> 21:28.287
People are eating a lot of it
right now.

21:28.370 --> 21:30.747
-I sell a lot of it.
-Cool.

21:30.831 --> 21:31.665
And, um--

21:31.748 --> 21:34.167
-It's delicious.

21:34.251 --> 21:38.005
It's dawned on me
that I've actually never known

21:38.088 --> 21:42.592
why black people don't want to be
associated with fried chicken.

21:42.676 --> 21:43.885
During enslavement,

21:43.969 --> 21:47.973
African Americans weren't frying up
buckets of chicken for ourselves, right?

21:48.056 --> 21:51.268
Platters of chicken. We were cooking that
for those who enslaved us.

21:51.351 --> 21:55.230
So, black people
started being associated with chicken

21:55.314 --> 21:58.442
and chicken products
in popular culture, right?

21:59.151 --> 22:00.986
Big lips, bulging eyes.

22:01.069 --> 22:05.407
The ways that those images
are described as cute, as fun,

22:05.490 --> 22:06.950
that's what makes them insidious.

22:07.034 --> 22:12.539
<i>That's what makes them evil.</i>
<i>And this is the only perception</i>

22:12.622 --> 22:15.042
that you have of black people and chicken.

22:15.125 --> 22:19.004
What's present-day examples of something
like this, which is horrifically sad?

22:19.087 --> 22:20.172
Well... Popeyes.

22:20.255 --> 22:22.132
Are you ready for a cooking lesson, honey?

22:22.215 --> 22:24.676
<i>She's a happy,</i>
<i>African American woman</i>

22:24.760 --> 22:28.555
<i>talking in a very Southern dialect,</i>

22:28.638 --> 22:32.559
<i>and the goal is to make everyone happy</i>
<i>with the fried chicken.</i>

22:32.642 --> 22:35.228
This is a meal
that will make your mama shout.

22:35.312 --> 22:40.108
So that's the modern day version,
really, of this kind of thing.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.527
I love Popeyes' chicken.
Yeah.

22:42.611 --> 22:43.904
But should I never eat this stuff?

22:43.987 --> 22:47.324
I mean, you could also see it
as the modern picture of this.

22:47.407 --> 22:49.367
Of black women selling chicken.

22:49.451 --> 22:53.246
<i>You can't tell me that these women,</i>
<i>though they were some of the first</i>

22:53.330 --> 22:56.833
African American female entrepreneurs
in Orange County, Virginia,

22:56.917 --> 23:00.212
probably didn't also smile
and play the role

23:00.295 --> 23:02.589
in order to get their food sold, right?

23:02.672 --> 23:07.886
So some of it is playing to the strength,
playing to the stereotype.

23:10.263 --> 23:12.641
I was doing
a fried chicken special on TV.

23:12.724 --> 23:14.684
Before we went on, my friend is like,

23:14.768 --> 23:17.604
"You're never gonna catch me
eating fried chicken on national TV."

23:17.687 --> 23:19.606
-And I didn't get it.
-Yeah.

23:19.689 --> 23:22.859
I didn't understand it and I don't think
I was really aware until I was...

23:22.943 --> 23:24.945
-Mmm-hmm. Mmm-hmm.

23:25.028 --> 23:28.865
Like, eating fried chicken
or, like, being told by...

23:28.949 --> 23:31.993
You know? "Don't eat fried chicken,
I will never eat fried chicken in public."

23:32.077 --> 23:36.873
A single black person carries the weight
of the black community on their back.

23:36.957 --> 23:39.501
<i>Because part of being black in America</i>

23:39.584 --> 23:44.256
<i>is you get often reduced to the stereotype</i>
<i>of angry, lazy, shiftless,</i>

23:44.339 --> 23:46.424
chicken-eating black person,

23:46.508 --> 23:49.636
and nobody wants to put themselves
out there in that way.

